net.fathomsoft.nova.tree

Class ReturnNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.TreeNode
      • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.ValueNode
        • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.ReturnNode

  • public class ReturnNode
extends ValueNode
    ValueNode extension that represents a return statement node type. See decodeStatement(TreeNode, String, Location, boolean, boolean) for more details on what correct inputs look like.

      • decodeStatement

        public static ReturnNode decodeStatement(TreeNode parent,
                         java.lang.String statement,
                         Location location,
                         boolean require,
                         boolean scope)
        Decode the given statement into a ReturnNode instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.

        Example inputs include:
        • return
        • return node
        • return 0
        • return getAge()
        • return age + 32
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a ReturnNode instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        scope - Whether or not the given statement is the beginning of a scope.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a ReturnNode.
